subSubSection.paragraph:
C o m m e n t: The original description is based on an unspecified number of 
syntypes
from "Zante (v. Kiesenwetter), 
Creta
(Zebe)" (
KRAATZ 1858
). According to Lutz Behne (e-mail 22 Aug., 2018) there is no type material in the Kraatz collection at the SDEI. The collection of Gustav Zebe was moved to "Hartmann/Arnswalde" around 1870 (
HORN et al. 1990
); the Kiesenwetter collection is deposited in the Zoologische Staatssammlung München. It does not seem likely that the former collection will ever be located, and no type material was found in München (Michael Balke, e-mail 7 Sept., 2018).

♂
: tergite VIII (
Fig. 2
) oblong, posterior margin acutely pointed; sternite VIII (
Fig. 3
) oblong and with convex posterior margin; median lobe of aedeagus (
Figs 4-6
) approximately 
0.45 mm
long, with long and slender, bisinuate (lateral view) ventral process.
